# Polylang — Internationalization Rules

## Active languages on kombomeals.rs
- Serbian (sr_RS) — default
- Russian (ru_RU)
- English (en_US)

## Plugin uses WordPress i18n + Polylang string registration
- All translatable strings: __('string', 'kombo-manager') or _e('string', 'kombo-manager')
- Text domain: kombo-manager
- Translation files live in: languages/
- File naming: kombo-manager-sr_RS.po / .mo, kombo-manager-ru_RU.po / .mo

## Polylang custom string registration
- Every custom string that is NOT in a PHP template must be registered via pll_register_string()
- Registration happens in: includes/class-i18n.php — method register_strings()
- Called on: plugins_loaded hook (already wired in main class)
- Never call pll_register_string() inline in random files — always goes through class-i18n.php

## String registration format
pll_register_string( 'unique-key', 'Default string in English', 'Kombo Manager' );

## Rules
- Never hardcode Serbian, Russian, or English strings directly in PHP output
- All admin notices, labels, error messages → go through __() or pll__()
- When adding a new user-facing string → add to class-i18n.php register_strings() immediately
- Frontend strings visible to customers → must be registered in Polylang so they appear in Polylang UI for translation
- Admin-only strings (manager/kitchen) → standard __() is enough, no pll_register_string needed

## Dynamic strings (e.g. order status labels)
- Define as array in class-i18n.php
- Run each through pll_register_string() on registration
- Retrieve with pll__() not __()